1
00:00:01,010 --> 00:00:03,010
(theme music)

2
00:00:03,010 --> 00:01:44,240
♪

3
00:01:46,270 --> 00:01:48,200
You're our enemy, Himura!

4
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:49,290
If I were to
let you live,

5
00:01:49,290 --> 00:01:52,080
then that would mean
death for the rest of us!

6
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:54,100
You're wrong, I don't
want to kill you.

7
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:56,000
Stop your lying!

8
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:01,290
♪

9
00:02:01,290 --> 00:02:05,050
(growling)

10
00:02:05,050 --> 00:02:08,070
(yelling)

11
00:02:08,070 --> 00:02:10,170
♪

12
00:02:10,170 --> 00:02:14,070
Dearest Lord, I beseech
Thee to accept my offering.

13
00:02:14,070 --> 00:02:17,000
The sacrifice of
Kenshin Himura's life

14
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,190
for Your good
and the good

15
00:02:18,190 --> 00:02:20,230
of all Your
Christian people.

16
00:02:20,230 --> 00:02:33,210
♪

17
00:02:33,210 --> 00:02:35,100
How strange.

18
00:02:35,100 --> 00:02:47,180
♪

19
00:02:49,020 --> 00:02:51,150
When you were a slasher,
you killed your fellow man.

20
00:02:51,150 --> 00:02:52,220
That's a mortal sin.

21
00:02:52,220 --> 00:02:54,060
You are evil and
must be killed

22
00:02:54,060 --> 00:02:56,020
to save the rest of us.

23
00:02:56,020 --> 00:02:57,160
You're wrong,
it's been ten years

24
00:02:57,160 --> 00:02:59,210
since I've killed a man,
I don't want to kill anyone,

25
00:02:59,210 --> 00:03:01,180
you're making a
terrible mistake!

26
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:02,170
You liar!

27
00:03:02,170 --> 00:03:04,140
You live to
serve the devil!

28
00:03:04,140 --> 00:03:05,230
Kaiou has told me.

29
00:03:05,230 --> 00:03:08,130
You're an evil
inhuman killer!

30
00:03:08,130 --> 00:03:09,270
Kaiou?

31
00:03:09,270 --> 00:03:11,250
Himura is evil incarnate,

32
00:03:11,250 --> 00:03:15,060
an inhuman monster trying
to destroy all that is good.

33
00:03:15,060 --> 00:03:18,180
He has been sent here
from hell to kill us all.

34
00:03:18,180 --> 00:03:21,020
(growling)

35
00:03:21,020 --> 00:03:23,210
All that is
evil must die!

36
00:03:23,210 --> 00:03:28,270
♪

37
00:03:28,270 --> 00:03:31,260
(barking)

38
00:03:31,260 --> 00:03:39,250
♪

39
00:03:39,250 --> 00:03:41,180
I tell you,
I am not evil!

40
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:43,280
Now let me go, I don't
want to kill anyone!

41
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:45,250
Quiet, liar!

42
00:03:45,250 --> 00:03:51,080
♪

43
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:53,240
(grunting)

44
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:55,270
♪

45
00:03:55,270 --> 00:03:58,010
You broke it.

46
00:03:58,010 --> 00:04:00,200
(growling)

47
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:04,210
♪

48
00:04:04,210 --> 00:04:06,070
Huh?

49
00:04:06,070 --> 00:04:09,090
♪

50
00:04:09,090 --> 00:04:12,110
(whimpering)

51
00:04:12,110 --> 00:04:14,250
No, stop it,
don't attack me!

52
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:16,250
(shouting)

53
00:04:16,250 --> 00:04:19,090
♪

54
00:04:19,090 --> 00:04:20,290
Now hold on,
we'll try to escape.

55
00:04:20,290 --> 00:04:22,100
Huh?

56
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:25,050
Quick, grab me.

57
00:04:25,050 --> 00:04:27,140
What do you mean?

58
00:04:27,140 --> 00:04:29,180
(grunting)

59
00:04:29,180 --> 00:04:38,100
♪

60
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:40,070
(panting)

61
00:04:42,270 --> 00:04:44,090
I don't get it.

62
00:04:44,090 --> 00:04:46,230
How come you helped me?

63
00:04:46,230 --> 00:04:48,150
You are an evil demon.

64
00:04:48,150 --> 00:04:49,110
Why didn't--

65
00:04:49,110 --> 00:04:50,290
I'm not an evil demon.

66
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:52,140
Like I've been
trying to tell you,

67
00:04:52,140 --> 00:04:54,270
I don't want to kill
or harm anyone.

68
00:04:54,270 --> 00:04:57,200
I'm just glad I could get
us away from those dogs.

69
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:59,150
Huh?

70
00:04:59,150 --> 00:05:01,180
Wow, looks like you
got a pretty nasty bite

71
00:05:01,180 --> 00:05:03,030
on your arm there, maybe--

72
00:05:03,030 --> 00:05:04,040
(gasping)

73
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:06,260
Hey, I'm just
trying to help.

74
00:05:06,260 --> 00:05:08,140
We had specially
trained those dogs

75
00:05:08,140 --> 00:05:11,140
so that they would attack
when they heard that whistle.

76
00:05:11,140 --> 00:05:15,040
You broke the whistle so
now we cannot control them.

77
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:18,040
You doing that is gonna
make Shogo awful mad.

78
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:19,210
You should've let
the dogs eat me

79
00:05:19,210 --> 00:05:22,020
'cause now I just
don't know what to do.

80
00:05:22,020 --> 00:05:22,359
Don't you see?

81
00:05:22,359 --> 00:05:24,090
Kaiou will kill me.

82
00:05:24,090 --> 00:05:25,270
Why?

83
00:05:25,270 --> 00:05:28,290
You saved my life
so I won't kill you.

84
00:05:28,290 --> 00:05:32,040
I've learned to reward
kindness with kindness.

85
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:36,040
I'm sorry that
I have to do this,

86
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,260
but please understand.

87
00:05:37,260 --> 00:05:40,120
(clanking)

88
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:42,170
Please stay here while
I go ask Lady Magdalia

89
00:05:42,170 --> 00:05:43,270
just what I should do.

90
00:05:43,270 --> 00:05:45,220
I'll be back soon!

91
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:46,220
Hey, wait!

92
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:49,230
I can't wait here!

93
00:05:49,230 --> 00:05:51,240
(audible sigh)

94
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:53,180
(barking)

95
00:05:53,180 --> 00:05:56,010
(shouting)

96
00:05:57,210 --> 00:06:00,100
(panting)

97
00:06:00,100 --> 00:06:02,270
♪

98
00:06:02,270 --> 00:06:06,130
(grunting)

99
00:06:06,130 --> 00:06:08,070
(audible sigh)

100
00:06:08,070 --> 00:06:09,180
Huh?

101
00:06:09,180 --> 00:06:12,160
♪

102
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,100
Bark all you want,
you half-brained hounds,

103
00:06:14,100 --> 00:06:15,100
'cause you'll never get me.

104
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:18,140
You mutts might as well
attack each other!

105
00:06:18,140 --> 00:06:20,030
If I were a dog,
I'd relieve myself

106
00:06:20,030 --> 00:06:21,050
right on your heads,

107
00:06:21,050 --> 00:06:23,130
you big-butted
barking buffoons!

108
00:06:23,130 --> 00:06:25,030
(laughing)

109
00:06:25,030 --> 00:06:26,090
Ah!

110
00:06:26,090 --> 00:06:28,000
Oh no!

111
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,290
♪

112
00:06:31,290 --> 00:06:34,040
(grunting)

113
00:06:36,050 --> 00:06:39,100
Why is that I always wind up
with the really tough jobs?

114
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:41,270
♪

115
00:06:41,270 --> 00:06:43,240
Agh!

116
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:48,140
♪

117
00:06:48,140 --> 00:06:49,190
(gulping)

118
00:06:50,260 --> 00:06:52,160
I should've known
this thing was cursed

119
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:56,000
when I gave it back and that
girl slapped me in the face.

120
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,210
(grunting)

121
00:06:58,210 --> 00:07:04,290
♪

122
00:07:04,290 --> 00:07:07,250
(shouting)

123
00:07:12,020 --> 00:07:13,140
Kori!

124
00:07:13,140 --> 00:07:16,100
Kori!

125
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:18,110
Darn it, something
must have happened,

126
00:07:18,110 --> 00:07:19,230
I just know it.

127
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:21,140
And I was supposed
to protect Kori

128
00:07:21,140 --> 00:07:23,200
while Kenshin was gone.

129
00:07:28,250 --> 00:07:30,090
Huh?

130
00:07:36,210 --> 00:07:38,220
Hey, wait a minute.

131
00:07:38,220 --> 00:07:41,130
That's Santo, the guy
I saw with Governor Elsten.

132
00:07:41,130 --> 00:07:44,130
Huh, why would he be
coming to Shimabara?

133
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:47,030
Well, he can't be
up to any good.

134
00:07:54,250 --> 00:07:58,290
Mr. Kaiou, I'm very pleased
that you invited us here.

135
00:07:58,290 --> 00:08:00,200
(chuckling)

136
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:13,080
♪

137
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,180
You must be the one.

138
00:08:14,180 --> 00:08:16,090
You're Shogu Amakusa.

139
00:08:17,290 --> 00:08:19,170
You are correct.

140
00:08:19,170 --> 00:08:21,080
And you must be
Himura's woman.

141
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:22,190
(gasping)

142
00:08:22,190 --> 00:08:25,140
♪

143
00:08:25,140 --> 00:08:27,040
Please, you must
explain to me

144
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:29,030
why you want
to kill Kenshin.

145
00:08:29,030 --> 00:08:32,020
Because it is
my fate to do so.

146
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:33,080
Why is it your fate?

147
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:34,110
Without question,

148
00:08:34,110 --> 00:08:37,090
Himura's Amakakeru
Ryu no Hirameki

149
00:08:37,090 --> 00:08:38,210
is the ultimate
sword technique

150
00:08:38,210 --> 00:08:40,090
that exists on Earth,

151
00:08:40,090 --> 00:08:41,230
but I have taken
that technique

152
00:08:41,230 --> 00:08:42,260
and raised
it to a level

153
00:08:42,260 --> 00:08:46,020
that is actually
above almighty Heaven.

154
00:08:46,020 --> 00:08:47,170
So this is my fate.

155
00:08:47,170 --> 00:08:50,000
My sword, which
is above Heaven,

156
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,270
must destroy Earth's
dominant sword

157
00:08:51,270 --> 00:08:55,220
so that Hiten Mitsurugi
can be redefined by me.

158
00:08:55,220 --> 00:09:01,210
♪

159
00:09:01,210 --> 00:09:04,180
So you really think you're
better than any other human?

160
00:09:04,180 --> 00:09:07,020
♪

161
00:09:07,020 --> 00:09:08,020
Well, you're wrong!

162
00:09:08,020 --> 00:09:09,120
You're a vain,
pompous man

163
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,270
and if you truly
understood Kenshin,

164
00:09:10,270 --> 00:09:13,000
you'd leave him alone!

165
00:09:15,020 --> 00:09:16,000
I really don't know

166
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,290
if you're a better
swordsman than Kenshin.

167
00:09:17,290 --> 00:09:20,040
Maybe it's absolutely
true what they say.

168
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:24,000
Maybe you are able to use
your sword like a god.

169
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:25,290
I don't care
how good you are.

170
00:09:25,290 --> 00:09:30,070
There's no way you'll
beat my Kenshin.

171
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:32,100
(water trickling)

172
00:09:32,100 --> 00:09:33,210
Because you are bad.

173
00:09:33,210 --> 00:09:36,140
You are nothing but an
evil merchant of death.

174
00:09:36,140 --> 00:09:39,000
You have said you come
in the name of God,

175
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:40,220
yet you try to
change people's minds

176
00:09:40,220 --> 00:09:43,100
by senseless killing!

177
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:45,220
(water trickling)

178
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:49,000
Hmm.

179
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,140
That's your opinion.

180
00:09:50,140 --> 00:09:52,170
But I must say
you're mistaken.

181
00:09:52,170 --> 00:09:53,240
Look to thyself.

182
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:55,080
Your leaders have
been responsible

183
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:58,050
for the deaths of thousands
of God-fearing Christians.

184
00:09:58,050 --> 00:10:00,010
I will avenge
an eye for an eye.

185
00:10:00,010 --> 00:10:02,000
It is time
for a baptism.

186
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:03,130
Uh, baptism?

187
00:10:03,130 --> 00:10:06,100
Once, long ago, God purged
the world of corrupt humans

188
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:07,210
by flooding the Earth.

189
00:10:07,210 --> 00:10:09,250
He left only a handful
of righteous people

190
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:11,170
to repopulate
the world.

191
00:10:11,170 --> 00:10:13,050
I will accomplish
the same thing

192
00:10:13,050 --> 00:10:14,250
in this decadent Meiji Era.

193
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:17,190
I will destroy this
country's corrupt authorities.

194
00:10:17,190 --> 00:10:19,260
This country will be
baptized in the blood

195
00:10:19,260 --> 00:10:21,270
of those evil men,
and I will be the one

196
00:10:21,270 --> 00:10:23,290
to choose who will
rebuild this nation.

197
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:26,170
And if you're lucky,
you will live to see it!

198
00:10:26,170 --> 00:10:28,090
You are insane if
you truly believe

199
00:10:28,090 --> 00:10:31,220
you have the right to
say who lives or dies.

200
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:35,000
Kenshin is
nothing like you.

201
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,000
He would never consider

202
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,280
killing anyone
to change things.

203
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:39,000
He knows that kindness

204
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,090
works much better than
brute force ever will.

205
00:10:41,090 --> 00:10:43,040
He's a man filled with
love and compassion

206
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:45,070
and you're nothing
but a monster!

207
00:10:45,070 --> 00:10:48,240
♪

208
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:50,100
(groaning)

209
00:10:50,100 --> 00:10:52,020
You dare you to
compare the child of God

210
00:10:52,020 --> 00:10:53,290
with the son
of a human?

211
00:10:53,290 --> 00:10:56,010
There is no comparison.

212
00:10:56,010 --> 00:10:57,230
(grunting)

213
00:10:59,140 --> 00:11:02,130
Why do you keep
staring at me?

214
00:11:02,130 --> 00:11:03,290
I'll tell you why!

215
00:11:03,290 --> 00:11:06,090
Your being a man of
God is beyond belief!

216
00:11:06,090 --> 00:11:07,180
Your eyes are
telling me

217
00:11:07,180 --> 00:11:09,170
something
completely different.

218
00:11:09,170 --> 00:11:13,190
♪

219
00:11:13,190 --> 00:11:15,130
(audible sigh)

220
00:11:15,130 --> 00:11:18,000
Now the time has come
for you to go tell him.

221
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:20,110
Tell Himura it's time
for his last fight.

222
00:11:22,050 --> 00:11:25,220
Ah, who are you?

223
00:11:25,220 --> 00:11:28,050
I'm Kori, Kori Kamiya.

224
00:11:28,050 --> 00:11:30,140
Kori Kamiya.

225
00:11:30,140 --> 00:11:32,100
(panting)

226
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:34,000
Boy, am I glad that
you're both here!

227
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,200
I need your help to
tell me what to do

228
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:38,050
about that guy back there.

229
00:11:38,050 --> 00:11:39,160
Just who do you mean?

230
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:42,000
I mean Battousai Himura.

231
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,160
(gasping)

232
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:57,220
I can't just wait here.

233
00:11:57,220 --> 00:11:59,070
It's been over an hour.

234
00:11:59,070 --> 00:12:01,100
Sano might be in trouble.

235
00:12:01,100 --> 00:12:03,210
But if I don't wait here
for Janoman to return,

236
00:12:03,210 --> 00:12:06,220
then Amakusa
might kill him.

237
00:12:06,220 --> 00:12:12,010
♪

238
00:12:12,010 --> 00:12:13,090
Kenshin!

239
00:12:15,030 --> 00:12:17,010
What are you doing here?

240
00:12:17,010 --> 00:12:20,160
♪

241
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:23,210
Whoa, how did you
break out of this chain?

242
00:12:23,210 --> 00:12:25,260
You could've just
walked away from here.

243
00:12:25,260 --> 00:12:27,050
Thank you.

244
00:12:27,050 --> 00:12:28,200
You are something.

245
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:31,100
This is another example of
why you'll never be great.

246
00:12:31,100 --> 00:12:32,160
To achieve greatness,

247
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:34,280
you must know that your needs
are above everyone else's.

248
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:36,220
You're just too
stupid to know that.

249
00:12:36,220 --> 00:12:38,090
Huh?

250
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:40,220
I begin to understand
you, Himura.

251
00:12:40,220 --> 00:12:42,140
You think of
other people first

252
00:12:42,140 --> 00:12:44,090
and you believe by
being kind to people,

253
00:12:44,090 --> 00:12:45,100
you can change
their hearts

254
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:46,210
and how they think.

255
00:12:46,210 --> 00:12:49,040
(thundering)

256
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:50,230
Well, I will prove
that your strength

257
00:12:50,230 --> 00:12:52,290
is really just
a weakness.

258
00:12:52,290 --> 00:12:58,120
♪

259
00:12:58,120 --> 00:13:00,110
Since Hiko told me
that you were a master

260
00:13:00,110 --> 00:13:01,270
of Hiten Mitsurugi style,

261
00:13:01,270 --> 00:13:04,210
I knew that a showdown with
you would be inevitable.

262
00:13:04,210 --> 00:13:07,030
But fighting you is
not why I am here.

263
00:13:07,030 --> 00:13:10,140
Defeating you
is not my goal.

264
00:13:10,140 --> 00:13:12,010
I have come here
not to fight,

265
00:13:12,010 --> 00:13:14,010
but, instead, I'm here to
teach you what you need

266
00:13:14,010 --> 00:13:17,280
to know about
human nature.

267
00:13:17,280 --> 00:13:20,250
Hiten Mitsurugi is meant
to protect the people.

268
00:13:20,250 --> 00:13:23,120
Protecting the people is the
real reason it was created

269
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:25,180
and the only way
to truly use it.

270
00:13:25,180 --> 00:13:26,290
This was not
only the belief

271
00:13:26,290 --> 00:13:28,250
of all the successive
Seijuro Hikos,

272
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:30,220
but it was also
accepted by Hyouei,

273
00:13:30,220 --> 00:13:32,240
who taught you
Hiten Mitsurugi.

274
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:34,150
Hiten Mitsurugi
was never used

275
00:13:34,150 --> 00:13:35,260
as an offensive technique,

276
00:13:35,260 --> 00:13:38,010
it is to defend,
not to attack.

277
00:13:39,290 --> 00:13:41,190
Here, I brought
this from Hyouei,

278
00:13:41,190 --> 00:13:43,120
he really wanted
you to have it.

279
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:47,140
This is his will, he gave
it to me on his deathbed.

280
00:13:47,140 --> 00:13:48,240
Uncle Hyouei?

281
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:51,100
♪

282
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:53,200
You must read this
before you fight me.

283
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:56,040
Wrong, I don't have
to read anything.

284
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:58,280
You don't seem to understand
that my Hiten Mitsurugi style

285
00:13:58,280 --> 00:14:00,000
is much more advanced

286
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:02,020
than your pathetic
defensive technique.

287
00:14:02,020 --> 00:14:04,100
I've taken it far beyond
the thought of any human,

288
00:14:04,100 --> 00:14:05,170
including Hyouei.

289
00:14:05,170 --> 00:14:08,130
Try to understand that for
the sword above heaven,

290
00:14:08,130 --> 00:14:10,250
all human thought
is meaningless.

291
00:14:10,250 --> 00:14:17,000
♪

292
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,080
Well, that's a shame.

293
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:20,080
Since that's
how you feel,

294
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:22,170
I'll just put Hyouei
here to watch us.

295
00:14:22,170 --> 00:14:37,090
♪

296
00:14:38,170 --> 00:14:41,140
(thundering)

297
00:14:45,090 --> 00:14:47,120
It's about to begin.

298
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:48,220
This is it.

299
00:14:48,220 --> 00:14:50,030
It's going to happen.

300
00:14:52,000 --> 00:15:02,250
♪

301
00:15:02,250 --> 00:15:04,150
Be sure to
watch carefully.

302
00:15:04,150 --> 00:15:07,220
Shogo's the one-and-only
sword above heaven.

303
00:15:07,220 --> 00:15:15,190
♪

304
00:15:15,190 --> 00:15:17,060
(thundering)

305
00:15:17,060 --> 00:15:19,160
♪

306
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:21,120
(yelling)

307
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:23,130
(gasping)

308
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:25,250
Is that your tornado
thrust technique?

309
00:15:25,250 --> 00:15:27,070
Well, it's my turn.

310
00:15:27,070 --> 00:15:28,100
Time for you
to see what a real

311
00:15:28,100 --> 00:15:29,290
tornado thrust
looks like!

312
00:15:29,290 --> 00:15:32,140
♪

313
00:15:32,140 --> 00:15:33,280
I've never seen
Hiten Mitsurugi

314
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:35,070
taken to such a level.

315
00:15:35,070 --> 00:15:36,240
His speed is
beyond God Speed,

316
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:39,050
it's more like
super God Speed.

317
00:15:39,050 --> 00:15:41,100
♪

318
00:15:41,100 --> 00:15:42,270
Twirling Ryunkansen.

319
00:15:42,270 --> 00:15:45,080
♪

320
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:46,240
Watch out!

321
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:51,080
Still standing, eh?

322
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:53,080
I see why they call
you a legend.

323
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:55,100
You really must be
a legendary swordsman

324
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:56,280
to withstand
my initial attack.

325
00:15:56,280 --> 00:15:59,220
There's no doubt that Shogo
is the sword of God.

326
00:15:59,220 --> 00:16:01,110
Now I see
what you mean.

327
00:16:01,110 --> 00:16:04,240
-Right.
-Kenshin, get ready!

328
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:08,030
Even Master Hiko would've
been surprised by that move.

329
00:16:08,030 --> 00:16:09,090
It was amazing to see

330
00:16:09,090 --> 00:16:11,160
that tornado thrust
with a twirl.

331
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:13,100
Considering your
incredible speed,

332
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:15,200
I expect your next
technique to be Ryusosen.

333
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:17,010
Hmm?

334
00:16:17,010 --> 00:16:18,090
But I don't
think my knowing

335
00:16:18,090 --> 00:16:20,140
what your next move
is will stop you.

336
00:16:20,140 --> 00:16:22,000
You're right, it won't.

337
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:25,040
But I want to see
your Ryusosen as well.

338
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:36,050
♪

339
00:16:36,050 --> 00:16:37,150
Let's do it.

340
00:16:37,150 --> 00:16:45,070
♪

341
00:16:45,070 --> 00:16:46,240
Here I am.

342
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:50,070
(grunting)

343
00:16:50,070 --> 00:16:52,070
Kenshin!

344
00:16:52,070 --> 00:16:54,070
(groaning)

345
00:16:54,070 --> 00:16:58,050
♪

346
00:16:58,050 --> 00:17:01,020
(whimpering)

347
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:03,010
(grunting)

348
00:17:04,270 --> 00:17:06,230
I know he's badly hurt,

349
00:17:06,230 --> 00:17:09,180
but his concentration won't
allow him to give up now.

350
00:17:09,180 --> 00:17:16,110
♪

351
00:17:16,110 --> 00:17:18,060
It's amazing that
you're able to control

352
00:17:18,060 --> 00:17:20,130
the power that
you possess.

353
00:17:20,130 --> 00:17:22,160
I'm sure that if you
had really wanted to,

354
00:17:22,160 --> 00:17:25,070
you could've finished
me off already.

355
00:17:25,070 --> 00:17:27,180
You could've cut off
my left arm completely

356
00:17:27,180 --> 00:17:29,000
if you had wanted.

357
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:31,230
Yes, but that wouldn't
have served my purpose.

358
00:17:31,230 --> 00:17:34,000
It would be meaningless
to have you die now.

359
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:35,020
I want you to show me

360
00:17:35,020 --> 00:17:37,080
the ultimate
swordsmanship on Earth.

361
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:39,200
♪

362
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:42,200
So you're going
to use Kuzuryusen.

363
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:44,000
Oh, Kenshin.

364
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,260
It looks as though
you're right.

365
00:17:45,260 --> 00:17:48,130
I guess Shogo wants to
see Kenshin try to counter

366
00:17:48,130 --> 00:17:51,240
with his Amakakeru
Ryu no Hirameki.

367
00:17:51,240 --> 00:18:04,000
♪

368
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,060
With his strength diminished,

369
00:18:05,060 --> 00:18:07,040
he can't use any
other counter technique

370
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:08,210
and Shogo knows it.

371
00:18:08,210 --> 00:18:10,190
This should be most
excellent, Himura.

372
00:18:10,190 --> 00:18:12,000
You have no
other move left

373
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:15,120
but your Amakakeru Ryu
no Hirameki death blow.

374
00:18:15,120 --> 00:18:17,120
Good luck.

375
00:18:17,120 --> 00:18:29,210
♪

376
00:18:29,210 --> 00:18:31,220
Time you saw the
sword from Heaven.

377
00:18:31,220 --> 00:18:33,250
♪

378
00:18:33,250 --> 00:18:36,100
Kuzuryusen.

379
00:18:36,100 --> 00:18:37,140
Get ready!

380
00:18:37,140 --> 00:18:39,190
(yelling)

381
00:18:39,190 --> 00:18:52,120
♪

382
00:18:52,120 --> 00:18:53,200
I can't believe it.

383
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:56,140
It didn't look like Amakusa
delivered a killer blow.

384
00:18:56,140 --> 00:18:57,260
Why not?

385
00:18:57,260 --> 00:19:01,050
(yelling)

386
00:19:01,050 --> 00:19:03,080
(gasping)

387
00:19:03,080 --> 00:19:04,180
Unbelievable.

388
00:19:04,180 --> 00:19:06,270
Kenshin countered
Amakusa's Kuzuryusen

389
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:09,020
with his own Kuzuryusen.

390
00:19:09,020 --> 00:19:15,010
♪

391
00:19:15,010 --> 00:19:16,050
I'm shocked.

392
00:19:16,050 --> 00:19:17,130
I thought I left
you no other move

393
00:19:17,130 --> 00:19:20,120
but your Amakakeru
Ryu no Hirameki.

394
00:19:20,120 --> 00:19:23,180
Why didn't you use that
to defend yourself?

395
00:19:23,180 --> 00:19:25,210
Because I had to show you
that the people of Earth

396
00:19:25,210 --> 00:19:27,090
sometimes lead
with their hearts.

397
00:19:27,090 --> 00:19:28,120
Huh?

398
00:19:28,120 --> 00:19:31,110
You cannot break the
human spirit, Shogo.

399
00:19:31,110 --> 00:19:32,190
What?

400
00:19:35,220 --> 00:19:39,120
(grunting)

401
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:41,150
(thundering)

402
00:19:41,150 --> 00:19:42,200
Now I will
give you a loss

403
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:45,000
that is even
worse than death!

404
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:50,040
♪

405
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:52,210
(thundering)

406
00:19:52,210 --> 00:19:54,110
(gasping)

407
00:19:54,110 --> 00:20:00,180
♪

408
00:20:00,180 --> 00:20:02,250
Eternal darkness!

409
00:20:02,250 --> 00:20:29,260
♪

410
00:20:34,210 --> 00:20:36,090
Kenshin, oh, no!

411
00:20:36,090 --> 00:20:39,280
(panting)

412
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:43,220
(waves crashing)

413
00:20:43,220 --> 00:20:45,190
He's gone!

414
00:20:45,190 --> 00:20:47,290
(sobbing)

415
00:20:57,160 --> 00:21:02,170
♪

416
00:21:02,170 --> 00:21:03,180
(audible sigh)

417
00:21:03,180 --> 00:21:19,070
♪

418
00:21:19,070 --> 00:21:20,080
(gasping)

419
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:22,240
No!

420
00:21:22,240 --> 00:21:23,270
Oh, Kenshin!

421
00:21:23,270 --> 00:21:25,230
Kenshin!

422
00:21:25,230 --> 00:21:27,280
(sobbing)

423
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:42,000
♪

424
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:44,090
Are you all right?

425
00:21:44,090 --> 00:21:45,070
Kori?

426
00:21:45,070 --> 00:21:47,030
(gasps)

427
00:21:47,030 --> 00:21:49,210
I'm sorry I
made you worry.

428
00:21:49,210 --> 00:21:51,260
I hope I haven't
caused you pain.

429
00:21:51,260 --> 00:21:53,200
Kenshin, I don't want
you to talk that way,

430
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:55,220
you're going
to be all right!

431
00:21:55,220 --> 00:21:58,130
Oh, I love you, Kenshin.

432
00:21:58,130 --> 00:22:00,230
I love you so much.

433
00:22:00,230 --> 00:22:02,100
You're gonna
be all right!

434
00:22:02,100 --> 00:22:04,140
It's you, Yoshi.

435
00:22:04,140 --> 00:22:07,040
It's really good
to hear your voice.

436
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:09,130
I'm glad you're both safe.

437
00:22:13,130 --> 00:22:15,220
Huh?

438
00:22:15,220 --> 00:22:17,060
I'll give you a loss

439
00:22:17,060 --> 00:22:20,010
that is even worse than
death itself, Kenshin.

440
00:22:20,010 --> 00:22:22,040
Eternal darkness.

441
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:25,140
(whooshing)

442
00:22:25,140 --> 00:22:28,270
And Amakusa attacked
me with Rairyusen

443
00:22:28,270 --> 00:22:31,140
and since then,
my eyes completely lost

444
00:22:31,140 --> 00:22:34,120
their power
to see forever.

445
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:38,030
What is it?

446
00:22:38,030 --> 00:22:39,220
Huh, Kenshin?

447
00:22:41,130 --> 00:22:42,210
What is it?

448
00:22:42,210 --> 00:22:44,010
Oh no!

449
00:22:44,010 --> 00:22:46,170
He can't see!

